Just as a follow up, I did pick up an EIDE controller (The Promise 2300+) 
and with it I was able to do exactly what I wanted, and then some...

I now have a 1-gig HPFS Boot partition,   (Drive 1)
             540-Meg HPFS Data Partition, (Drive 2)
             350-Meg FAT Games Partition, (Drive 3)

And I have a place to add a 4th Drive, all on this one card, and OS/2 
sees it all...Even booting under a DOS Floppy lets me see the FAT drive 
which is actually the 3rd drive on the system...

Quite nice...The only drawback with the Promise Card is the OS/2 drivers 
supplied do not work with WARP, and Promise sez they will have one RSN 
(Been saying this since Nov..), but the standard driver seems to work 
fine, but Im sure a 'native' driver would give a nice speed increase, but 
untill that comes out, Im very happy with the performance provided by the 
standard driver...


