In <3k9h34$hce@news.cais.com>, rono@cais3.cais.com (Ron Olshavsky) writes:
>Hey all,
>
>  If I put an EIDE controller in my box, and hook up a 1-gig drive, will 
>this get around the 1024 cylinder boot-partition problem?
>
>  Will I need a special driver for the EIDE controller, or will the 
>standard driver work...
>
>  Anyone have any EIDE Controller recomendations?

Yes, in fact, I have: The Promise EIDE2300+ is a great controller. No
problems at all with OS/2 (but you may need to change a jumper).
The EIDE2300 needs no drivers, it simply "patches" the BIOS.
There are some drivers supplied, but they doesn't make any speed change
(According to NU SysInfo, my HD, a WD720, gives me 2200kB/sec with
or without the drivers), weird thing really. And don't try them, they only
ruin your HD...

Hoped that helped you!
